abstract: Russia's President Vladimir Putin and Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan will discuss Ankara's offer to provide military support to Libya's internationally recognized government during talks in Turkey next month, the Kremlin said on Tuesday.
snippet: Russia's President Vladimir Putin and Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan will discuss Ankara's offer to provide military support to Libya's internationally recognized government during talks in Turkey next month, the Kremlin said on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — Russia's President Vladimir Putin and Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan will discuss Ankara's offer to provide military support to Libya's internationally recognized government during talks in Turkey next month, the Kremlin said on Tuesday.
headline_main: Russia and Turkey to Discuss Libya Military Support in January: Kremlin
headline_print_headline: Russia and Turkey to Discuss Libya Military Support in January: Kremlin

abstract: Police fired shots in the air and volleys of tear gas to push back thousands of demonstrators in the Indian capital New Delhi on Tuesday as protests raged against a new citizenship law that has angered the country's Muslims.
snippet: Police fired shots in the air and volleys of tear gas to push back thousands of demonstrators in the Indian capital New Delhi on Tuesday as protests raged against a new citizenship law that has angered the country's Muslims.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — Police fired shots in the air and volleys of tear gas to push back thousands of demonstrators in the Indian capital New Delhi on Tuesday as protests raged against a new citizenship law that has angered the country's Muslims.
headline_main: Police and Protesters Clash in Indian Capital Over Citizenship Law
headline_print_headline: Police and Protesters Clash in Indian Capital Over Citizenship Law

abstract: Turkish authorities have arrested a mayor from Turkey's main opposition party over his alleged links to a U.S.-based Muslim cleric, the state-run news agency reported Tuesday. Separately, c lose to 200 people were detained in other police operations.
snippet: Turkish authorities have arrested a mayor from Turkey's main opposition party over his alleged links to a U.S.-based Muslim cleric, the state-run news agency reported Tuesday. Separately, c lose to 200 people were detained in other police operatio...
lead_paragraph: ANKARA, Turkey — Turkish authorities have arrested a mayor from Turkey's main opposition party over his alleged links to a U.S.-based Muslim cleric, the state-run news agency reported Tuesday. Separately, c lose to 200 people were detained in other police operations.
headline_main: Turkey: Opposition Mayor, Others Arrested Over Ties to Coup
headline_print_headline: Turkey: Opposition Mayor, Others Arrested Over Ties to Coup

abstract: The Pakistani court’s sentence is unlikely to be carried out because Mr. Musharraf is no longer in the country.
snippet: The Pakistani court’s sentence is unlikely to be carried out because Mr. Musharraf is no longer in the country.
lead_paragraph: ISLAMABAD, Pakistan — After years of delays and disruptions, a special court in Pakistan on Tuesday sentenced the country’s former military dictator, Pervez Musharraf, to death in a treason case.

abstract: A Malaysian police officer on death row for the 2006 slaying of a Mongolian model has accused former prime minister Najib Razak of ordering him to kill the woman, according to media reports and the policeman's lawyer.
snippet: A Malaysian police officer on death row for the 2006 slaying of a Mongolian model has accused former prime minister Najib Razak of ordering him to kill the woman, according to media reports and the policeman's lawyer.
lead_paragraph: KUALA LUMPUR — A Malaysian police officer on death row for the 2006 slaying of a Mongolian model has accused former prime minister Najib Razak of ordering him to kill the woman, according to media reports and the policeman's lawyer.
headline_main: Malaysia's Najib Ordered Killing of Mongolian Model, Says Former Bodyguard
